The capture command, cap, creates a new session by capturing audio
from the sound card.  If your mixer settings are right, simply type cap
and press enter at a prompt.  You can press any key to stop capturing.
If you need to change mixer settings when starting the capture, type cap,
a space, and the word line, mike, or wave, and press enter.  Edway will
look for and run a script named capline.edw, capmike.edw, or capwave.edw
in that case.  The script capstop.edw is run when capturing stops.
These files must be executable, and may be placed in any directory on
the execution path, such as /usr/local/bin.

